cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on software protection and preventing reverse engineering and tampering attacks. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper presents an architecture and tool flow for renewing parts of native applications dynamically. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses code diversification and renewal techniques. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the renewed and diversified code and data are delivered from a secure server to a client on demand. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is also relevant as the paper presents a prototype implementation and evaluates it on industrial use cases.
